<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="E" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Examine" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Examine,</orth> 1) to inspect carefully, to inquire into, to explore: <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.3.67" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 3, 67</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 1.1.291" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado I, 1, 291</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 2.3.216" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 3, 216</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 1.1.68" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. I, 1, 68</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 1.89" default="NO" valid="yes">John I, 89</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.1.69" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 1, 69</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.1.153" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 1, 153</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 1.1.234" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 1, 234</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 1.3.83" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 3, 83</bibl>.<lb />2) to interrogate as in a judicial proceeding: <bibl n="shak. ado 3.5.51" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado III, 5, 51</bibl>. 64 (Qq <emph>examination</emph>). <bibl n="shak. ado 4.2.6" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 4.2.6" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 6</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ado 4.2.6" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 6</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ado 5.1.322" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 322</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 4.1.203" default="NO" valid="yes">As IV, 1, 203</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.413" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 4, 413</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.2.105" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 2, 105</bibl>.
<lb />3) to question, to doubt: <cit><quote>all her deserving is a reserved honesty, and that I have not heard --d,</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 3.5.66" default="NO" valid="yes">All's III, 5, 66</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>